Leadership Academy (LeAd) 2017/2018

Published on Jul 18, 2017

Leadership Academy (LeAd) 2017/2018


Leadership Academy (LeAd) 2017/2018

The Leadership Academy (LeAd) is an elected student leadership body whose purpose is to serve and lead the students to care, love and support a positive SOTA community.

The Academy comprises 3 branches - Class Management Council (CMCC), Community and School Culture (COMMS) and Leadership Studies Committee (LSC).

LeAd empowers students to pursue leadership opportunities which will enrich the SOTA community and grow the skills and experiences of the student leaders. To achieve these, LeAd supports student-organised events that are both meaningful and essential to cultivate and sustain a positive school culture and identity rooted in the values of humility, integrity, people-centredness and passion.

Some upcoming events in our calendar for 2017/2018 include National Day Celebrations, Teachers’ Day, Fire Works Action and our inaugural Leadership Conference in 2018.
